{
  "stem": "3964.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And by January of 1939, my father and I were directed to go to work to build a underground-- be a laborer-- to build an underground airport for the German army or air force at that time.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "This airport was approximately 35 kilometers away from my hometown.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "We had to get up every morning at 4 o'clock, go to work.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And the type of work, kind of labor we performed was carrying bricks.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "From 7 o'clock in the morning till 5:00 in the afternoon, my dad and I, as well as other Jews who were there, carried bricks.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "There we no dollies to carry them on.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "We had no protective clothing to wear, no gloves to wear to protect our hands.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And obviously, having not been used to it-- and I was a little boy.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "I was 13 years old-- my hands were very tender.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And after the first day, I had bloody hands carrying these bricks approximately maybe 400, 500 yards from one place to another.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "Nevertheless, it was not an excuse not to go to work the next day, because our food rations we were getting and my parents-- my mother was getting, my aunts were getting-- dependent on my father and myself going to work and doing that type of work.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "It was very difficult, very hard.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "But as I said earlier, my father always had a positive attitude, which fortunately I inherited from him.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And we talked a lot to each other and said, we just have to keep on going.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "Hopefully things change.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "I don't really know if any one, my father, made any serious effort to leave or to-- to escape.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "I know there were some efforts made to immigrate to the United States.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
